- `dixon_coles_tau` — pure function, 5 branches covering the four ≤1 scorelines and the `1.0` default
- `decay_weight` — `0.5^(age/half_life)` exponential decay, works on scalars and arrays
- `DixonColesEstimator.fit` — weighted MLE via L-BFGS-B; ρ bounded to `(-0.99, 0.0]` to keep τ safe; τ floor at `1e-10`; mean-zero attack normalization enforced post-fit with intercept compensation
- `score_matrix` — applies τ correction then normalises by `mat.sum()` so the truncated pmf always sums to exactly 1.0
- `ScorelineSampler.sample` — `np.random.default_rng(seed)` + `rng.choice` on the flattened pmf, default seed from `PoissonConfig.random_seed`
- `_prepare` uses `.isna()` on nullable `Int64` columns before `.astype(int)` to avoid cast errors

